# Ingredient Name Formatting: AP-Style Title Case

All ingredient names stored in the `ingredients` table must use **AP-style Title Case**.

## Rules

- Capitalise the first word and all major words
- Keep these words lowercase (unless they start the name): a, an, the, and, but, or, nor, for, yet, so, of, in, to, on, at, by, with, from, as, per, vs
- Examples: "Soy Milk", "All-Purpose Flour", "Salt", "Tomato Paste", "Extra Virgin Olive Oil"

## Where this applies

- **Recipe import** (`parse-recipe.ts` system prompt already instructs the LLM to return Title Case names)
- **Ingredient creation** (`apply-plan.ts` runs `toTitleCaseAP()` on every new ingredient name before inserting)
- **Manual ingredient add** in the inventory UI
- **Any future code** that inserts into `ingredients.name`

## Implementation

Use `toTitleCaseAP()` from `@/lib/ingredient-resolution/normalize` whenever creating or renaming an ingredient. Never store lowercase or ALL-CAPS ingredient names.
